headline: Kids do not want to go to child-free weddings either
text: At the child-free wedding, the guests were seen frantically checking their watches, not because they were related to the bride and groom, but because they were hoping to catch the dessert before it disappeared!
There's a flower in my garden that decided to grow on the roof, but it wasn't too bad — at least it has a hammer to help with its high-flying lifestyle!

There was a pumpkin that needed some work, so it went to the drill. The pumpkin said, "Carve me up a nice face!" And the drill replied, "Sure thing, I've got a jackhammer drill bit just for pumpkins like you."
There was a laptop who fell off the desk and broke open. Turns out, it had been avoiding its hammer for years, thinking it was just a tool and not a potential friend in need of software updates.
There was a spray bottle that decided to move into the fridge. Every morning, it would wake up covered in sticky notes reminding it, "Don't forget to chill!"
There was a pepper in the kitchen who decided to deseed his life entirely, but all he ended up with was a lot of empty caps and some surprising holes.
There was a laptop that needed a drill. Not because it had a hole in it, but because it wanted to create some much-needed ventilation during its intense gaming sessions.
There was a banana walking in the park, and it saw a sign that said "No Peel or Spray." The banana thought, "Well, I guess I'll just have to air freshen my own problems."

There was a haunted pumpkin patch that needed de-ghosting, so they hired a team of ghostbusters. The first thing the lead ghostbuster did was spray some holy water—oops, I mean pumpkin spray—across the area. It turned out to be just a really soggy ghost!
There was a shirt that loved to roll down hills, but its owner was always too busy ironing out plans to notice.
There's a sign in the laundromat that reads, "Wash Your Laptop Here"—but no one follows it because who leaves their laptop in the washing machine by accident?

There was a roller who loved bananas so much, he had a banana split tattooed on his roller skate. He said it brought him so much joy, he could literally roll with it whenever he saw a bunch of bananas!
There was a shirt that loved to shake hands with everyone, but when it came to shaking off the dampness after a summer storm, it found the clothesline too far to clothe itself.
There's a new haircut trend where people measure their hair before cutting it. One guy measured his and found it was only an inch long, so he decided to measure again just to be sure!
There was a barber who tried cutting hair while sitting on a chair, but he kept falling off because the "cut" of his style made him lose balance!
There was a bicycle that needed a wash, but it never got any cleaner—turns out it was too lazy to pedal its way to the river!
There was a time when my blend of casual and formal shoes decided to have a fashion rebellion, and now they won't stop swapping styles mid-day!

There was a sign at the beach that read, "No moving towels allowed." One towel moved over to another and said, "Why did you move?" The other replied, "I didn't want to be a stationary object in a world of constant move."
There was a laptop that caught a cold and decided to stay inside. It was so isolated that when it needed to communicate, it used a spray bottle to send messages like "Pass the Wi-Fi!"
There's a drill in my book club, but instead of discussing novels, we're going through pages one by one with a power tool!
There was a keyboard in the office that kept getting sprayed with water, but it never complained—it just learned to type underwater!
There's a new trend in home organization where people use measuring tape not just for accuracy, but also to ensure their fridge doors can close properly after adding yet another jar of pickles.
There was a chicken trying to measure its steps across the farm but kept trodding on eggs, wondering if it needed to recalibrate its step meter or lay down some more markers.
There was a chair that couldn't sit still; it preferred to shake things up during meetings, much to the annoyance of its coworkers.

There's a new beverage on the market called CornBlend, and it's causing quite a stir at breakfast tables. People are blending their corn with everything from smoothies to coffee, but one couple decided to blend their corn together and ended up with a surprisingly tasty side dish for their steak!
There was a tomato that needed a drill, not because it wanted to make sauce, but because it heard being hole-y could be quite the fashion statement in the summer garden club.
